<p style="text-align:justify;">from age become useless to the community, are released from the miseries of life by being drowned, or otherwise dispatched.  They resemble the Laplanders in many points, and are, if possible, more ignorant and brutal.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Nova Zembla.  The Indians of this Country are still more brutal and ignorant than the Samoiedes or any of their neighbours.  The men have little or no hair <span class="AddHand-author">upon their</span> heads, but the beards are strong and bushy: the women have long hair falling down in plaids on their shoulders &#8211; and adorn their ears and noses with pendants of blue stone and fish bones &#8211; having their chins and foreheads painted with blue streaks.  The men, when they fish, dress in seal skins; the tails of which hang dangling down between their legs.  Their food is the beasts they kill in hunting, and the fish they catch along the shore.</p>

